create_time.description: Creation time of this resource. A timestamp in RFC3339 UTC "Zulu" format, with nanosecond resolution and up to nine fractional digits. Examples: "2014-10-02T15:01:23Z" and "2014-10-02T15:01:23.045123456Z".

gateway_id.description: The canonical identifier of the logical router that this subnet is attached to.

gateway_ip.description: The IP address of the gateway of this subnet. Must fall within the IP prefix defined above.

ip_cidr_range.description: The IP address range of the subnet in CIDR format.

name.description: The ID of the subnet. For userDefined subnets, this name should be in the format of "service-n", where n ranges from 1 to 5.

parent.description: The resource name of the private cloud to create a new subnet in. Resource names are schemeless URIs that follow the conventions in https://cloud.google.com/apis/design/resource_names. For example: projects/my-project/locations/us-west1-a/privateClouds/my-cloud

standard_config.description: Whether the NSX-T configuration in the backend follows the standard configuration supported by Google Cloud. If false, the subnet cannot be modified through Google Cloud, only through NSX-T directly.

uid.description: System-generated unique identifier for the resource.

update_time.description: Last updated time of this resource. A timestamp in RFC3339 UTC "Zulu" format, with nanosecond resolution and up to nine fractional digits. Examples: "2014-10-02T15:01:23Z" and "2014-10-02T15:01:23.045123456Z".

vlan_id.description: VLAN ID of the VLAN on which the subnet is configured.
